  "description": [
    "Between The Lines BY DEAN GORDON B HANCOCK FOR ANP EISENHOWER WAS PITIFUL IN RICHMOND When the Virginia Dixiecrats tricked Gen Dwight D Eisenhower into coming to Richmond so shortly after Gov Adlai Stevenson ap peared here they did him a great disservice Eisenhower was lamen table and even pitiful in camparison with the eloquent and states manlike Stevenson It was like the proverbial chalk and cheese or like tipping off an evening of champagne with coco cola Eisenhower was in water over his head when he attempted to speak in the wake of an Adlai Stevenson who had everything a great political occasion might call fornamely eloquence wit and states manlike presentation First of all Stevenson struck everyone even his hecklers as in tellectually honest He did not try to bypass the civil rights issue for it is the core of the souths political motivations The South today can be roughly divided into two camps one favoring civil rights and the other opposing them The campaign revolves once more around the Negro issue that has vexed the south through many generations The state rights proponents are no more than polite opposers of civil rights After all the south must"
